'''Shit on a shingle''' (sometimes abbreviated S.O.S.) is a [[U.S. Armed Forces]] [[slang]] term for chipped [[beef]] on [[toast]]. Due to the (largely) unfavorable reaction to the "cuisine" provided them, the U.S. soldiers during [[World War I]] coined this term of "affection."

